Locations.Notes:
The laboratory department at Sharp Coronado Hospital is open daily. No appointment is necessary, but a physician's order is required.
All patients should go directly to the laboratory department for registration and testing.

Please note that fasting is required for lipid panel and rheumatoid factor, and is recommended for the comprehensive metabolic panel (CMP) and the basic metabolic panel (BMP). Lab results for complete blood count (CBC) and chemistry test panels are faxed, called or delivered to the referring physician's office within 24 hours.
 
Why choose Sharp Coronado's lab services?
·         If you or a loved one has a disability or mobility challenge that makes it difficult to visit our laboratory for blood draws, call our team to arrange a "drive-through phlebotomy" appointment, where our technicians can meet a patient in front of the hospital and draw blood from the comfort of his or her car
·         Our laboratory technicians offer free hand massages to relax and comfort patients before they have blood draw

Physicians.Bio:
My father was a veterinary doctor and my mother a pharmacist. This exposed me to the wonders of science at a young age. Combined with the satisfaction and fulfillment from helping others, the practice of medicine was a clear choice for me. I am a board-certified shoulder, elbow and sports surgeon. With medical and orthopedic surgery training from the Mayo Clinic, University of Pennsylvania and Columbia University, where I assisted the team doctors for the New York Yankees, I strive to provide a superior level of skill and empathetic care to each and every individual. I deliver the same care to my patients as I would to a family member.

I enjoy volunteering and participating in charity when I am not at work. Staying fit and healthy is important to me; I run, lift weights and play basketball. I am passionate about traveling, reading and cooking.
